INSERT INTO `Hardware` (`HardwareID`, `HardwareName`, `HardwareNameQualifier`, `HardwareManufacturer`, `HardwareModel`, `HardwareSerialNumber`, `HdwManufDateQualifier`, `HardwareManufactureDate`, `HardwareSignificance`, `HardwareComments`, `ImageLocation`) VALUES ('Hrd0021', 'Teleprinter ASR33', 'with paper roll', 'Teleytype Corporation', '3380 6JC', '27-004-F02', 'c1960s', NULL, 2, 'with paper roll and tape.\r\nThese machines were 1960s versions of teletypes, hence they were descendants of the Flexowriters used with CSIRAC.  They are effectively four devices in one - keyboard, printer, paper tape reader and paper tape punch.  These devices could be used independently, ie printing could be accompanied by punching a paper tape or not as required.  This made them suitable as input/output devices for early mini-computers.  They operated at 10 characters per second and generally used 8 bit ASCII characters and 8 channel paper tape.', 'db_img/Hrd0021.1.JPG;db_img/Hrd0021.2.JPG');
