INSERT INTO `Media_Storage` (`MediaID`, `HrdID`, `MediaObjectName`, `MediaObjectNameQualifier`, `MediaManufacturer`, `MediaDate`, `MediaProvenance`, `MediaSignificance`, `ImageLocation`, `MediaComments`) VALUES ('CScM0024', NULL, 'EDSAC Film 16mm', NULL, 'Cambridge University', '1951/1976', 1, 2, 'db_img/CScM0024.JPG', 'In 1949 Maurice Wilkes at Cambridge University, built EDSAC and established the first computer service. This film about EDSAC and the pioneers at Cambridge, made by Wilkes in 1976 and incorporating film made in 1951, is a record of the earliest days of computing.\r\nIt is also remarkable for the similarity in its style to the CSIRAC film.\r\nHttp://sms.cam.ac.uk/media/739532');
INSERT INTO `Media_Storage` (`MediaID`, `HrdID`, `MediaObjectName`, `MediaObjectNameQualifier`, `MediaManufacturer`, `MediaDate`, `MediaProvenance`, `MediaSignificance`, `ImageLocation`, `MediaComments`) VALUES ('CScM0025', NULL, 'EDSAC Film video copies', 'Copies of 16mm film CScM0024 x2', NULL, NULL, 1, 1, 'db_img/CScM0025.JPG', 'In 1949 Maurice Wilkes at Cambridge University, built EDSAC and established the first computer service. This film about EDSAC and the pioneers at Cambridge, made by Wilkes in 1976 and incorporating film made in 1951, is a record of the earliest days of computing.\r\nIt is also remarkable for the similarity in its style to the CSIRAC film.\r\nHttp://sms.cam.ac.uk/media/739532\r\nThese are video copies of the EDSAC film CScM0024. Copied on behalf of the Computer History Group 2005.');
INSERT INTO `Media_Storage` (`MediaID`, `HrdID`, `MediaObjectName`, `MediaObjectNameQualifier`, `MediaManufacturer`, `MediaDate`, `MediaProvenance`, `MediaSignificance`, `ImageLocation`, `MediaComments`) VALUES ('CScM0026', NULL, 'Video Mudpac  and Babbage Exhibition', 'At', 'Museum Victora', 'September 1994', NULL, 1, 'db_img/CScM0026.JPG', 'Recorded at Applied Science, Museum of Victoria, Abbotsford 1994.\r\nInterview with Eric King-Smith, talking about Mudpac. (54 mins)\r\n0-00-00 to 0.54.06 SVHS format \r\n0.54.27 to 1.48.30 VHS format\r\nAlso contains:\r\nBabbage Exhibition, Science Museum, London. Feb 1993.\r\n1.48.35 to 1.52.50 (4-1/4 min).');
